tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function, and mildly increased alkaline phosphatase and HDL cholesterol. Total protein is slightly low, but albumin and globulin are within range. Liver enzymes and other electrolytes are normal. Findings are most notable for possible chronic kidney disease; correlation with clinical context and further renal evaluation are recommended.
